<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><strong><font color="#f90909" size="5">The Beverly City School District is Closed.</font></strong></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:center;"><font color="#fd0505">School will be open every Monday for the duration of the closure to pick up food between the hours of 10:00 AM and 11:00 AM.<br>​High school students who are in need of food are welcome.</font></div>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:center;"><font color="#fd0505" size="5">The schedule is as follows:</font></div>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:center;">
<font size="5" color="#fd0505"><strong>April 20 - 10:00 -11:00 AM Work/Food Pick Up</strong></font><br><font size="5" color="#fd0505"></font>
</div>

<div class="paragraph">
<span>Dear Beverly City Families:</span><br><br><span>I hope everyone enjoyed the break and trust all are faring well. We received word from our Governor, Phil Murphy, that we will in fact need to extend our school closure until at least May 15, 2020, at which time we will be reassessing the situation under strict guidance from the Governor and the decision to reopen will be based on careful discussion with our public health and safety experts.</span><br><br><span>This is a reminder that Monday, April 20 from 10:00 AM - 11:00 AM we will be passing out:</span><br><br><ol>
<li style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34)">Breakfasts and lunches for the week.</li>
<li style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34)"><span>Paper packets to the families who indicated to the homeroom teachers that they do not have access to the internet in their homes. There are 22 students who fall in this category.</span></li>
<li style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34)">
<span>Chromebooks to those students who previously indicated they needed one to their homeroom teacher over the phone. If you did not indicate that you needed one, there will not be one available for pick-up. Prior to pick-up, you must complete the "Student Chromebook Contract" available at the link found below of this message.</span><br>​<span>This form can be completed from a Smartphone. You will not be permitted to pick up a device without completing this form prior to your arrival on April 20. There are 109 students who fall in this category.</span>
</li>
</ol>
<br><span>If you are using your own device, you do not need to complete this form. This form is only for students who indicated that they will need to borrow a chromebook. Again, if you told your homeroom teacher when they called or emailed that you have a device to use at home, there will not be one available for you to pick up. </span><span>There are 187 students who indicated they have a device at home and do not need to borrow a computer</span><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0)">. </span><span>We are trying to limit the number of students who need to return to school on April 20 to ensure everyone’s safety. </span><br><span>If you later decide that you in fact need to borrow a chromebook, you will need to contact the school and arrange for a date to pick-up, but do not come on April 20.<br><br>The window for pick-up is a one hour time slot. This will be the only pick up for the week. Going forward, meal and work pick up will only be available on Mondays from 10:00 - 11:00.<span> </span> </span><br><span>With regard to the previously completed work packets, please hold onto these. We will be collecting and grading all completed packets upon our safe return to school. </span><br><span>Third marking period grades will reflect the work the students completed up to their last face-to face classes, which was March 13th. These 3rd marking period grades will be adjusted to reflect new grades once home packets are returned and graded. 4th marking period grades will be a pass/fail system. Attendance will be taken daily for our virtual learners and weekly for our paper packet learners. </span><br><span>If anyone has any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out either via email or phone. Phone messages are checked several times throughout the day and someone will return your call within 1 school day. Email messages are checked frequently throughout the day and all employees are working virtually every school day from 8:15AM - 3:15PM  following the school calendar. </span><br><span>Be apart now, so we can all be together later. Stay safe!</span><br><span>Sincerely,</span><br><span>Elizabeth C. Giacobbe, Ed.D.</span>
</div>

